    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/1343</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shidehara</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the American Ambassador in Japan</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Castle</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="28" xml:id="d108fn28">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Ambassador as an enclosure to his despatch No. 109, January 20, 1931;
                        received February 7.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-24">May 24,
                            1930</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 66/T1</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of
                    your Note dated May 21, 1930,<note n="29" xml:id="d108fn29">
                        <hi rend="italic">Proceedings of the London Naval Conference</hi>, p.
                        297.</note> relative to the interpretation of the term “category” <pb
                        facs="0207" n="127" xml:id="pg_127"/> appearing in Article 19 of the London
                    Naval Treaty of 1930.</p>
                <p>The Imperial Government understands the word “category” appearing in Article 19
                    of the above-mentioned treaty to mean “category” or “sub-category;” thus, it
                    interprets this treaty in the sense that ships belonging to either sub-category
                        (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) or sub-category (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) of the
                    cruiser category (Article 16) which shall become over age may be replaced only
                    within that sub-category.</p>
                <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baron Kijuro Shidehara</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>[<hi rend="smallcaps">seal</hi>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
